Inheritance;
is a inheritance in Java through which one class acquires the properties and methods of
another class;.
why we should use Inheritance:
1) it helps reduce the amount of the code that we have to write;
2)it is more efficient;
3)Save memory;
How we can  use Inheritance;
we can use the extends keyword after the class name and then the same of the class
from which we want to inherit the code. Example is given below.
Types of inheritance;
